<h1>Problem 2356 - 2023 India National Olympiad, P3 of 6, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Find all real numbers \(c\) for which there exists
  a function \(f : \mathbb{N} \to \mathbb{N}\) such that
  <ul><li>for all integers \(x \ge 1\) and \(a \ge 2\),
  the fraction \(\frac{f(x+a)-f(x)}{a}\) is not an integer;</li><li>for all integers \(x \ge 1\), we have \(|f(x)-cx|<2023\).</li></ul></p>
